summary: ✗ - Has your muse ever been a victim of friendly fire or been betrayed during a fight? How did they react? -  Nines
question: ✗ - Has your muse ever been a victim of friendly fire or been betrayed during a fight? How did they react? -  Nines
answer:
Blaster shots rang out over the trenchline, causing soil and rock to spray up. One man dropped as a well placed beam of heat penetrated his eye socket. He made no sound, for the shot had pierced straight to his brain. A quick death, at least.

Nines was not a fan of trenches or battlefields. She was Imperial Intelligence, she shouldn’t have to attend places like this. But occasionally she got called upon to act almost as a commissar of sorts, a political officer there to keep the peace and prevent defeatism.

Three times she had to act before the desertions stopped. 

Once: A gaggle of soldiers refused to go over the top. They were shot.

Twice: A man injured himself repeatedly, hoping to be sent home. He was used as a minesweeper.

Third: A group of soldiers stuck in a fox hole were trying to retreat. They dived from hole to hole before getting pinned just ten meters from friendly trench lines. Nines had a squad set up post at the closest un-barbed section of the line to wait for them.

Eighteen hours later, when they were finally able to make it back under the cover of an artillery barrage along the enemy line, each was lined up against the wall and executed.

When one asked why, she answered bluntly:

“Deserters get shot.”

Oh the irony her future would bring.

From then on, people stopped deserting and instead started trying to get her killed.

Eventually the Chiss was removed from political duty as she was deemed more of a danger to her own troops than enemy fire. Except for over-the-top actions, more men died in her section of the line to officially sanctioned punishments than to enemy attacks, and significantly more than any other section of the Imperial trench network.

blog.name: verrader-is-dutch-for-traitor
blog.title: Ignorance is for other people
blog.description: you will be able tell your children what you've been here the whole time

body:
The return of the WHO?

I can’t believe I never realized that George Martin wasn’t the only one who draw inspiration from The Lord of The Rings. I mean, of course, he wasn’t, but I just assumed he was the only one who was so open about it, BUT. Apparently I was wrong. What is the title of the third and final book/movie about Frodo? The RETURN OF THE King. Aaaaand what’s the title of the third and not so final movie about Luke Skywalker? Yes, it’s RETURN OF THE Jedi. It’s like they didn’t even tried to be original and I love them for it.

summary: Episode 4 - Gay Space Nerds   Join Alec and Meagan as we discuss (daa daa dadada daa) STAR WARS  through a queer lens. We’ll be...
body:
Episode 4 - Gay Space Nerds

Join Alec and Meagan as we discuss (daa daa dadada daa) STAR WARS through a queer lens. We’ll be deep diving into all of our favorite Star Wars characters and what it might have looked like if they were queer.

Content warnings: May/December relationships, anti-Kylux, Alec’s “singing” voice, Han Solo’s booty, incest mention, granny space lesbians

Mentioned in this episode: Luke Skywalker, Leia Organa, Han Solo, Lando Calrissian, Padme Amidala, Anakin Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi, Rey, Finn, Poe Dameron, Chirrut Imwe, Baze Malbus, various droids

Suggested in this episode: Star Trek: Discovery, Saga
